<DocsLayout title="buoy dock" description="Dock Buoy into your project">
  <h1>buoy dock</h1>

  <p>
    Dock Buoy into your project by creating configuration files and setting up
    integrations. Auto-detects your framework and suggests optimal settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy dock [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-f, --force</code></td>
        <td>Overwrite existing configuration</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-n, --name &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Project name</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--skip-detect</code></td>
        <td>Skip auto-detection and create minimal config</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-y, --yes</code></td>
        <td>Auto-install recommended plugins without prompting</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--no-install</code></td>
        <td>Skip plugin installation prompts</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--hooks</code></td>
        <td>Setup pre-commit hook for drift checking</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Example</h2>

  <pre><code>$ buoy dock

Detecting project configuration...

Detected:
  Framework: React
  Styling: Tailwind CSS
  Components: src/components/

Creating buoy.config.mjs...

✓ Created buoy.config.mjs
✓ Added .buoy/ to .gitignore

Buoy is now docked! Run 'buoy sweep' to scan your codebase.</code></pre>

  <h2>With Hooks</h2>

  <pre><code>$ buoy dock --hooks

...
✓ Created .git/hooks/pre-commit

Pre-commit hook installed. Drift will be checked before each commit.</code></pre>

  <h2>Generated Files</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>buoy.config.mjs</strong> - Main configuration file</li>
    <li><strong>.buoy/</strong> - Local data directory (added to .gitignore)</li>
  </ul>

